<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Coulteria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Coulteria" order="Fabales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Coulteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Tara" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tara" order="Fabales" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Tara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its racemose inflorescences of unisexual flowers (vs. inflorescences of racemes and panicles with bisexual flowers), chartaceous to papyraceous, laterally-compressed, oblong to elliptic (occasionally suborbicular) stipitate pods, subtended by a 4-13 mm long stipe (vs. indehiscent, laterally compressed but slightly turgid and somewhat fleshy, coriaceous, straight, oblong, sessile pods), and compressed, ovate-orbicular to sub-quadrate, compressed (vs. ellipsoid) seeds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
